  <front>
   <head>The RECANTATION: To the same Lady.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">me, fair One, nor resent</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Lines to you I lately sent.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They seem, as if your Form you priz'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And ev'ry other Gift despis'd:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When a discerning Eye may find,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Your greatest Beauty's in your Mind.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
